{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770886141,"nonce":"FJWwAit/mepA7wULF/MLmv2HAnE=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDORKr0287qSBli","github-url":"https://github.com/bonanzahq/bonanza/issues/42","origin":"github"},"title":"Relocate Verwaltung link from user dropdown to main navigation","message":"The 'Verwaltung' (management/settings) link is currently hidden inside the user avatar dropdown menu alongside user-specific items like 'Account bearbeiten' and 'Abmelden'. Users expect only user-related actions under their profile icon, not application-level settings.\n\nVerwaltung contains application-wide settings:\n- Artikel anlegen (create articles)\n- Verleihende verwalten (manage lenders)\n- Werkstattinfos bearbeiten (edit workshop info)\n- Werkstatt vorübergehend schließen (temporarily close workshop)\n- Rechtstexte bearbeiten (edit legal texts)\n- Statistik (statistics)\n\nThese should be accessible from the main navigation, not buried in a user menu. Rethink placement - e.g. a dedicated nav item, a gear icon in the header, or a sidebar entry.\n\nAffected file: app/views/shared/_user_menu.html.erb\nOnly shown to users with manage permission on current_department.","files":null}]}